    <h2 id="api-reference">API Reference</h2>
    <div class="api-reference">
        <p>The <code>animation</code> option accepts either a symbol (predefined animation name) or a hash with the following properties:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>name</code> (Symbol or String) - Animation name. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>:bounce</code>, <code>:pulse</code>, <code>:scale</code>, <code>:shake</code></li>
                    <li><code>:fade</code>, <code>:slide</code>, <code>:ripple</code>, <code>:rotate</code></li>
                    <li><code>:swing</code>, <code>:pop</code>, <code>:jello</code>, <code>:wobble</code></li>
                    <li><code>:heartbeat</code>, <code>:rubberBand</code>, <code>:flash</code>, <code>:tada</code></li>
                    <li><code>:custom</code> - For custom animations with properties</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>trigger</code> (Symbol, optional) - When to start the animation. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>:hover</code> (default) - On mouse hover</li>
                    <li><code>:click</code> - On button click</li>
                    <li><code>:load</code> - When component loads</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>duration</code> (Number, optional) - Animation duration in seconds (default: 1.0)</li>
            <li><code>delay</code> (Number, optional) - Delay before animation starts in seconds (default: 0)</li>
            <li><code>timing</code> (Symbol, optional) - Timing function. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>:linear</code>, <code>:ease</code>, <code>:ease_in</code>, <code>:ease_out</code>, <code>:ease_in_out</code></li>
                    <li><code>:cubic_bezier</code> - Requires additional properties</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>iteration</code> (Symbol or Number, optional) - Number of times to play. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li>Number (1, 2, 3, etc.) - Play specific number of times</li>
                    <li><code>:infinite</code> - Loop forever</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>direction</code> (Symbol, optional) - Animation direction. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>:normal</code> (default) - Play forward</li>
                    <li><code>:reverse</code> - Play backward</li>
                    <li><code>:alternate</code> - Forward then backward</li>
                    <li><code>:alternate_reverse</code> - Backward then forward</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>fill_mode</code> (Symbol, optional) - What to do when animation ends. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>:none</code> (default) - Return to initial state</li>
                    <li><code>:forwards</code> - Keep final state</li>
                    <li><code>:backwards</code> - Apply first keyframe during delay</li>
                    <li><code>:both</code> - Combine forwards & backwards</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>properties</code> (Hash, optional) - Custom animation properties:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>transform</code> - CSS transform value</li>
                    <li><code>cubic_bezier</code> - Array of 4 numbers for custom timing</li>
                    <li>Any valid CSS property for custom animations. You can see the list of valid CSS properties     <a href="#valid-css-properties-for-custom-animations" data-level="3">here</a></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

